# Quiz Logic (Updated)

## Questions

### Q1. What best describes you right now?
- Student
- Employed (full-time or part-time)
- Gig worker / freelancer
- Homemaker / not working outside home
- Recent grad / between jobs

### Q2. Do you have a bank account in your own name?
- Yes
- No

### Q3. Do you have a credit card in your own name?
- Yes
- No

### Q4. Are you an authorized user on someone else's credit card?
(spouse, parent, family member)
- Yes
- No
- Not sure

### Q5. Do you know your credit score?
- Yes
- No

### Q6. Have you ever applied for credit and been rejected?
- Yes
- No
- Never applied

### Q7. Do you pay any regular bills?
(rent, phone, utilities, subscriptions)
- Yes, in my own name
- Yes, but under someone else's name
- No bills in my name

### Q8. What is your main goal?
- Start building credit from scratch
- Understand why I was rejected
- Build credit independently from my spouse/family
- Improve what little credit I have

---

## Result Logic

### Starting From Zero
IF:
- no bank account AND
- no own card AND
- no authorized user AND
- no known score

### Thin File Beginner
IF:
- has bank account OR authorized user
- no own card
- no rejection

### Rejected / Unsure
IF:
- rejected = Yes

### Early Builder
IF:
- has own credit card
- no rejection

### Homemaker / Dependent Income  ← new
IF:
- Q1 = Homemaker
- no own card
- bills not in own name OR authorized user only

OUTPUT focuses on:
- building independent credit
- secured card in own name
- authorized user benefits and limits
- why independent credit history matters
